Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper proposes a new ensemble of rateless FEC codes and analyzes their performance using information-theoretic tools such as weight enumerating functions and Shannon limits. 
2. cs.CC (Computational Complexity): The paper discusses the design and optimization of the Kite codes, which involves solving computational problems related to low-density parity-check codes. 
3. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The proposed FEC codes can be used in various networking and communication systems to improve the reliability of data transmission. 
4. cs.SI (Sound and Image Processing): The paper mentions the use of the proposed codes in multimedia applications, which may involve processing of sound and image data. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper discusses the use of the proposed codes in multimedia applications, which may involve transmission and storage of multimedia data.
